social_posts.post_text: What the golf closet looks like (and no, these are not all golf shoes and yes, I do have a sneaker problem).
@gur.design is coming along! Shout-out to the whole team for taking this from a fun idea to a legit business and to everyone who has trusted us this year with the logo work. 2023 is going to be fun!
One of my favorite rounds of the year with this crew @aomer1534 @ngwoodruff @pierre_omer
I actually hit a fairway!!! Miracle.

He’s a former professional golfer, a TV personality and author of THE GOLFERS ZOO — give a warm welcome to Shane Bacon. Shane joins us to share lessons and stories from his life in golf. Lessons include anecdotes from his stint as a caddy at The Old Course at St. Andrews to his days as a Mini Tour Professional.

As always, you can listen on your preferred listening service or watch on YouTube. Links in my bio!

The best trip of my year with the best dudes in the world. Crazy how fast 3 days goes by when you anticipate it for 360 days. 

Love these fellas. Lucky to have them as pals. Tubac ‘23 in the books.

Awesome couple of days at the PGA Show meeting and chatting with clients we have worked with or are working with for @gur.design … what started as @99kate_smith reimagining logos of courses she played has turned into a real, legit business and I’m blessed and happy to be a part of it. 

Also, shout-out @glenn_stroh for coming along and seeing what the Show is all about. 

Great, rewarding week!

First time playing CC of Charleston and loved every minutes of it. Made a good pass at this one on No. 11 which is nice because every miss on that hole is bad news.

The TOUR’s #Netflix series is right around the corner. Wrap your mind around all the action as @shanebacon and @kclairerogers recap everything that unfolds on the Full Swing Tonight Podcast.

Ep.1 breakdown drops this Wednesday, Feb. 15, on Skratch YouTube.

Spieth and JT are the focus of the PGA TOUR’s first Netflix episode and, yes, *the* photo makes an appearance.

@shanebacon and @kclairerogers dive in on the Full Swing Tonight Podcast. Link in bio.

@joeldahmen stops by and delivers some strong behind-the-scenes goods to @shanebacon and @kclairerogers on the Full Swing Tonight Podcast. Link in bio!
We think @mattfitz94 may have found his catchphrase. Fill in @shanebacon’s beep with @kclairerogers on this Full Swing Tonight Podcast. Link in bio.

I’ve been a huge fan of @seamusgolf for a long, long time. If you check out the second image you’ll see a post I wrote for CBS Sports about the company back in 2012 after coming across one of their headcover at Bandon Dunes (a headcover I still have and happily rock). 

So, you can imagine how pumped I am to be a part of a limited launch of the Bacon Breakfast Collection that drops on Friday with Seamus. 

A @gur.design designed headcover with our own coffee from the awesome folks at @goodwalkcoffeeco and a bacon ball-marker. 

A perfect purchase for those that agree breakfast is the best meal of the day. 

Link in my bio. It’s limited so if you want one, act now!

An awesome episode to get you hyped for the Masters with 3-time champ Nick Faldo. We discussed all three of his wins including that wild Sunday in 1996.

Big shout-out to @zachary_blair … this golf course is so fun and so unique. People will be enjoying it for decades and decades to come.

Golf trips are planned. Itineraries locked in months in advance. Sometimes years. 

But it’s these moments that make the trips. Already had a 36-hole day, dogs are seriously barking, you’re sunburnt and wind burnt and exhausted, but you pull the minivan up by the putting green, turn the high beams on and play for $20 a man.

Epic trip to Pinehurst with @joel_klatt @ashdonwoods @aomer1534 and a huge thanks to @homeofamericangolf for the help. Podcast recap coming soon at @getagrippod
Epic trip with the fellas. @homeofamericangolf is a special, special spot.
Is the PGA Championship the most exciting major in golf? @kyleportercbs and I chat about just that on the latest @getagrippod

We are excited to announce golf broadcaster, @shanebacon, as a PING Brand Ambassador and co-host of the new PING Proving Grounds Podcast. Learn more about Shane now and catch episode 1 on Thursday.

🥓🎙️🧠 TOMORROW. A podcast taking you inside the PING Proving Grounds with @jertybird, PING’s VP of Fitting & Performance, and @shanebacon, our newest brand ambassador. Tune in as they dive into all things golf to help you #PlayYourBest.

Subscribe at the link in our bio.

Exciting news - teaming up with my man @jertybird for the new PING Proving Grounds podcast.

The goal? To make this complicated game a little easier to understand + interesting guests + players + club builders and more. 

(And yes, I was tempted to take a gold putter after the first episode but I resisted the urge.) 

First episode drops tomorrow. Download/subscribe where you get your pods and/or hit the link in my bio.
🚨 Episode 1 🚨 of the PING Proving Grounds Podcast is available now at the link in our bio. Tune in to hear more about what goes on at the PING Proving Grounds from hosts @jertybird and @shanebacon.

Some images from the Ike this week at my home club. 71-71-66 for a T-7. Won the team event with @tilleygolf + Pops walked all 54 holes with me (what an animal). Fun week for sure. (📸 via @mga1897)
A quick equation for better set gapping. Catch this rule-of-thumb and more in this week’s podcast episode: A Guide to Gapping with @shanebacon and @jertybird. Head to the link in our bio to listen.
Harlow always playing a little defense at the Griddle.

Golf doesn’t allow us a lot of wins. Today was one of those.

Thrilled to be playing in my first U.S. Amateur at the ripe age of 39. 

The Am was actually the first time I ever hosted golf on national television back in 2016. That was a pinch-me moment. So is this. 

Shout-out to the @mga1897 and the @usga and my guy @kriley1138 for all the help. Pumped for 🍒
If there’s ever an episode that you should watch, it’s this one. We’re inside the PING Gold Putter Vault discussing the product development process. Watch or listen at the link in our bio.
The 8th green at @speybaygc is wicked. So is that weather rolling in. @linksgolfofficial
Sankaty is swweeeeeet.
A few shots from around Sankaty Head a day ago. Very, very special spot and a bucket list place for me.

Sensational time last week being a part of history with @pjkoenig … the man is going for the most rounds of golf in a calendar year and @brooklawncountryclub was his 319th round. 

Awesome dude, awesome crew, awesome RGV.

I played like a donkey but my mom and dad (and uncle) walked all 36 holes with me this week which is much cooler than any great round of golf. My sister, nephew and Uncle Dougie also came out and watched. They came to watch me fulfill a dream even if that involved a lot of missed five-footers. I’m a lucky dude. Now back home to a wife and little kiddos that do not care what I shot!
Marshal did me dirty on this one - hit the fairway on the 14th! Big thanks to everyone that came out and watched this week. Wild experience.
Fun episode this week with the 61 man himself, @viktor_hovland … subscribe/download the @pingtour Proving Grounds podcast wherever you get your pods.

You better make a good swing when a pro like @nitties23 is on the call.

social_posts.post_text: Hole-in-one #2 and it came at the @csgalinks mid-am. Good time to dial it in.

A lot of love for the latest @getagrippod with @joeldahmen and @genobonnalie talking about the worst swings/decisions of their career. Not many pro athletes would have this much fun rehashing the bad so shoutout to Joel and Geno for the time.

Loop life. There’s just nothing quite like it. 

I went on a journey to understand the world of caddying inside and out, presented by @FedEx. First stop, we met up with longtime caddie, Oscar, at scenic @golfkohler’s Whistling Straits.

Full episode is live! Link in my bio.

Episode 2 of Loop Life is out! I traded in my clubs for a bib and some lessons on how best to caddie from an Evans Scholar at Blue Mound. Watch the full episode via the link in my profile @skratch @fedex

The last episode of Loop Life with @skratch is live! Out at @erinhillsgolf I had the opportunity to play a few holes and then caddie a few holes. Did I pull off an amazing cartwheel at any point? Watch to find out! Link in my profile. @fedex

Some images from our time shooting Loop Life with @skratch and @fedex … I loved the opportunity to jump into world of caddying at some really cool spots and tell those stories. 

Check the link in my profile for all 3 episodes.
After a year+ of trying to hit it straight I’ve decided to go back to only hitting cuts (with the occasional pull-hook in there for good measure)
Backyard traj fun.

In honor of Halloween @shanebacon and @jertybird are debunking a few of the scariest shots in golf. Tell us your most-feared shot and tune in this week to become better prepared the next time you tee it.

Listen to the full pod at the link in our bio.

Inspired by the drink & cigar holders at the Drumlin at @erinhillsgolf, I asked @seamusgolf to create something similar for the Griddle. They absolutely knocked it out of the park; drink holder, cigar grooves, an abacus scoring system for closest to the pin battles.

So, so cool. Big thanks to the team for turning this silly idea into an awesome addition to the backyard.

Unreal few days at @streamsongresort … the Chain is a special short course that’ll be a ton of fun to tack on the back of a morning round at Black/Red/Blue.
Not going to be a lot of shorts golf in my world for the next couple of months … missing @streamsongresort
